caption: I’m seeing these posts saying the food at San Pablo’s has no taste... are we living in the same reality? I can’t get enough of this place! I think they have great food the lamb is flavorful. Get the street corn!
Dope corner spot. Outdoor and indoor seating
It was ok for me
My new #1 tacos place. Heidi was a peach. Thanks for the excellent service and food
Solid Mexican food. Street corn is everything you want it to be, Queso is tasty and not runny, Chorizo is spicy and flavorful work well with the pineapple. Definitely a nice fit for the area!
Hugh Burrito. Excellent specials.
Food has no flavor. Wait times was long.
Not sure. Didn't dtstvtiveat to rcadck
COLONIZED TACOS AT ITS BEST. I was so disappointed. If you’re looking for authenticity go else where.

I love this place. But not sure why they are accepting online orders at 11:30am on a Monday for a 12:30 pick up. I arrived at 12:15, they were not open. No one would answer the phone and the store was still closed at 1. Hoping my money gets refunded ASAP.

I want this place to make it so badly and this is probably the 6th time I've given them a chance. It was amazing when it first opened! The second time was slipping, and since then the menu has been halved and completely changed. I can barely tell the different taco meats apart and the shrimp (my favorite type of taco) is just.. not it. From what I understand this location doesn't have a real kitchen so I understand the limitations and I have to assume that the original menu wasn't sustainable. I just don't want to pay "city" prices for tacos that aren't really that good even if it's convenient. I'm really hoping for the best, though!
Thanks for letting us charge our skateboards! Great food!
This place is solid! The guac is some of the best I’ve gotten in Baltimore, and the rice and beans were flavorful. The veggie tacos were not incredible but pretty decent. The staff was very friendly!

I was actually on my way to a  big chain restaurant that sold the same food. I saw the unique store front that caught my eye as I was coming to a stop light. I saw the words street Taco’s and stop in. Filippo take my order and was very pleasant and answered all my questions as a new Patron. Bradon made the order quickly and also give off good vibes. I grabbed three tacos 2 chicken and 1 beef. The tacos was great and fill in good natural favors. The meal was light on my stomach which allowed me not to over eat. San Pablo’s offers flour tortilla which is a plus. All in all this is a good place to try and I know you won’t be disappointed.
I love me some tacos in this place have some of the best tacos and  Maryland I will be back real soon 😋 💪🏾
Delicious tacos
Excellent
They make good tacos its. Quesadillas are quite nice as well. Great indoor and outdoor seating.
Food was below average, customer service was not genuine and way over priced. What a very unpleasant experience.
Not many tables. Served in carry out cardboard. Taco were very good.
You can’t go wrong with the land chipotle tacos or the mushrooms and onions. Great staff great management overall very nice environment!! I will definitely be coming back and recommending this place.
Revised menu, good change. Barbacoa burrito hit the spot. Fast, friendly service. Nice outdoor seating
Tacos were decent, but overpriced when you add toppings. I recommend patronizing a shop owned/operated by Hispanic folx rather than random white guys. Location is convenient.

Very delicious! I got the Mexican street corn and lamb tacos with rice and beans. The manager had great suggestions and everything tasted as advertised. Cool location and great atmosphere. Everything seemed spaced well and clean. If I'm back in town, I'd definitely come back.

went on Tuesday for $2 taco Tuesday’s and had a great experience. We got chorizo, lamb and braised short ribs and it was all delicious. The pineapple on the chorizo was our favorite part!  They’re also dog friendly and gave our pup some treats! :)

If you’re ever in the Baltimore area, you neeeed to eat at San Pablo Street Tacos!!! The Queso is BOMB, and the Short Rib taco will change your life!!! Also, the restaurant/artwork is super cute!!!  Certified from a Texan who loves their Queso and tacos 💕💕💕
Had the birria and carnita tacos which were both outstanding— very flavorful, fresh, and savory. Probably among the best I’ve had.
The food was subpar and hard to eat. I would not recommend the food here. The service was friendly and fast, though! I appreciate that they adhered to covid protocol.
The tacos were not put together, everything was sloppy and they forgot to add shrimp on my SHRIMP tacos. are you guys high? Worst tacos ever.
Great food excellent service

I have really loved having San Pablo in the neighborhood! They have provided wonderful service since their opening recently, especially considering all of the changes recently. I love their tacos and burritos, and they have great options for plant-based eaters. Their in-house sangria is also to die for and a great price. As a Mexican-American, I'm always looking for a yummy experience when eating Mexican and Tex-Mex food --they do not disappoint. Am excited to see if they expand to include desserts on their menu.
Very helpful service
great street corn! (elote)

Was really good a when it opened with an awesome happy hour and great tacos. Just went tonight and it was completely different in a bad way. The tacos were bite sized and cost about 4$ per taco, their happy hour was gone, and the food tasted awful. Not going back until the menu changes to the old menu.

I went when they first opened. They had a full menu and margaritas to go! But recently I went and they cut the menu in half. Down sized the tacos, dropped the alcohol beside a fridge full of beers and white claw and kept the the above average prices. So for two people to get 3 tacos (and 3 of their tacos equals about one at Taco Bell) you’ll be paying about $25. $30 if you tip.

People these days really have no patience! Lots of undeserved 1-2 star reviews. First and foremost I want to commend San Pablo and it's staff for managing to open in the middle of a pandemic which has to be tumultuous at best! I've eaten here about once a week since they've opened because they deliver within a few blocks and I've never had a bad meal OR a bad experience with the staff. The opposite has been the case. Excellent food, don't mind the menu change up while they're figuring out what works best for them and the area. Keep up the great work!
Bland and sad food. Worst part is the crumbling and stale corn tortillas. The menu sounds so promising, but it's not good and it's mad overpriced.  Melody Cafe was better.
Came here on a whim for a quick snack! Staff was helpful, manager was pleasant. The shrimp garlic tacos were good and the street corn was bomb! I plan to return when back in Baltimore.

This place was horrible. Small tacos with no authentic Mexican condiments to put on the taco. The lamb taste like roast beef and the chicken take like shredded pork. The food was just horrible. I would not recommend going here for any tacos.

Excellent tacos. The rice and beans were great as well. Enjoyed the chips and queso. Want to try the guac. Manager was nice and gave me his card to let him know how everything was. Great addition to the neighborhood.

I recently went here with 2 friends since we heard the menu was updated and we were not disappointed. All 3 tacos we got were delicious and unique. Servers were very friendly and tacos came out fast. Definitely plan to go back. Outside tables could use an updating too, but not worth removing a star.

I had high hopes.  If you're paying $3.50 per taco, you expect quality, right?  This food is embarrassing.  Their tacos are small and the flavors are weak.  Their $4 side of rice (about 8oz) had no flavor whatsoever.  They didn't even toast the corn tortillas.  This place won't last, and good riddance to them.  This food isn't hard or expensive to make, so stop being lazy with your recipes and ridiculous with your prices.

definitely not worth it. $4-$5 per taco for the smallest tacos I've ever seen, and they weren't even very good. very bland, minimal effort. if i got these from a food truck, I'd be disappointed. they just use a subway sandwich shop style oven to heat everything up, which is REALLY slow. they didn't grill the tortillas or anything either. Sweet 27, taqueria sabor, tijuana tacos, or R&R are all better AND cheaper.

Brand new restaurant and they have already changed chefs. The chicken seemed boiled and bland and couldn't finish the tacos; had to throw them out. The Sriracha carnitas were decent flavored. The staff was very nice, but the manager a little too eager and in your face With some tweaks or with the old chef, I might consider coming back.

The food was alright. Like others have said, it just kinda misses the mark. The meats are mostly bland. The flour tortillas were alright, but like others have said just tasted cold and right out of a bag. We called in our order and even had it repeated back to us and it was still wrong. It was an okay experience, just probably wouldn't go back

i’ve been three times now. i do really like the chicken tinga tacos - especially prepared in the authentic style. yum. it’s a new spot and so they are reworking their menu a bit still. i would say some of the sides needed a bit of tweaking, but, as someone who cooks a lot and almost always prefers eating at home, i will still always appreciate the ability to scoop up some yummy tacos that are seemingly prepared from fresh, quality ingredients. all without having to dirty my own kitchen. i will be returning regularly.

I feel this place is missing the mark ! I have been here two times and both times disappointed. Tacos are average at best. Corn taco shell fell apart. Out of margaritas the 2nd time I went. If they plan to stay around the quality needs to go up a lot! I wont be back again until I hear it as improved. suggestion: think about serving margarita flights.

The good: shrimp, grilled fish, and flour tortillas were all fresh and quite good. The bad: the fried fish, rice, and chicken tinga were not great. The real problem: the corn tortillas are not fresh. They taste straight out of the bag and no effort was made to improve them. Even 30 seconds in a pan would help. I will probably return, but only get flour tortillas. And that's a shame. I love good corn tortillas.

This place... is not it. For some reason, I keep going back to give them another chance. I've been there multiple times, and every time I'm disappointed. I really wanted to like them but honestly, the food just isn't very good.
Delicious  tacos.  Loaded with beef,chicken and shrip.

I was excited about this place and was super disappointed. The corn tortilla was stale and my order was wrong. Everything was dry, there was no sauce on any of the meats that I ordered. The food was cold (even though I had just picked it up) and the shrimp and fish seemed like they were boiled or steamed? Lightly heated up in the oven at best. They do not seem to have a deep fryer nor a grill which are so crucial to good tacos. Go to Papi's for much fresher tacos and go to Clavel if you want something authentic. Also, the guacamole had sunflower seeds in it? I hope they figure some things out but I definitely will not be back.

This spot is new, the staff and service are friendly.  I really wanted to love it but the food didn't land for me. the crispy taco shell was soft and fell apart. the tacos were cold when we got them home. The rice and beans weren't flavorful. the decor was pretty cool though.  Traveler and Adventurer - IG @brian.dent
A much needed food establishment in Mount Vernon! Awesome place!

I really wanted to like this new place but I’m so disappointed. People were very nice, but the food is what I came for and it was subpar. The corn tortilla was stale and crumbled in my hands and even though they have a sophisticated order system what they put in the bag was incorrect. If they are still in business in a few months I might try them again to see if they have worked the kinks out of their kitchen.
Fast and friendly service and the mushroom tacos are soooo good!!
Friendly enough staff, fast service, and the Fish Pico Burrito was pretty damn good.👍
Excellent tacos, burritos, and service!
Great spot, great food. Glad to have some Mexican food in Mt. Vernon. Definitely stop by!
